items.title: Educational Neuroscience
items.headline: Brain Education
objectives_summary: Mind Brain and Education is an emerging scientific field that brings together researchers in cognitive neuroscience, developmental cognitive neuroscience, educational psychology, educational technology, education theory, and other related disciplines to explore the interactions between biological processes and education. Researchers in educational neuroscience investigate the neural mechanisms of reading, numerical cognition, attention, and their attendant difficulties. The aim of educational neuroscience is to generate basic and applied research that will provide a new trans-disciplinary account of learning and teaching, which is capable of informing education.
